    "Id": 1,
    "Content": "# claude.sh\n\nClaude Code rewritten as a bash script. ~1,500 lines. Zero npm packages.\n\n## Why\n\nThe original Claude Code is ~380,000 lines of TypeScript with 266 npm dependencies. This does the same core job in bash with just `curl` and `jq`.\n\n## Features\n\n- **Real-time streaming** via FIFO pipe â€” text appears as Claude generates it\n- **6 tools**: Bash, Read, Edit, Write, Glob, Grep\n- **Tool chaining** â€” up to 25 tool calls per turn\n- **Permission prompting** â€” asks before running non-safe commands (`y/n/a`)\n- **CLAUDE.md loading** â€” reads project instructions from CLAUDE.md files up the directory tree\n- **Git-aware context** â€” branch, status, and recent commits in system prompt\n- **Session save/resume** â€” auto-saves on exit, resume with `--resume <id>`\n- **Retry with backoff** â€” exponential retry on 429/529 rate limits\n- **Cost tracking** â€” per-turn and session totals\n- **Spinner** â€” with the original spinner verbs (Clauding, Flibbertigibbeting, etc.)\n- **Slash commands** â€” `/help`, `/cost`, `/model`, `/clear`, `/save`, `/resume`, `/commit`, `/diff`\n- **Pipe mode** â€” `echo \"explain this\" | ./claude.sh`\n\n## Install\n",
    "ContentSha": "GVk4JcgtpIBv8bt9ApLRdNbTkq2XYolFkKG7z0ouLtc=",
